# @podlite/editor-react

=head1 Upcoming

=item fix Enter in C<=item> list and Tab/Shift-Tab level change now scroll the cursor into view — previously the caret could move past the viewport bottom without scrolling. Same fix applied to image paste/drop insertion
=item add C<includeReader> and C<includeBaseDir> props — forwarded to the default preview C<<Podlite>> renderer so C<=include file:X> resolves at preview time. Hosts that supply a custom C<makePreviewComponent> are responsible for forwarding these themselves. Without C<includeReader> the directive renders as nothing (preserves the prior behaviour). Type C<IncludeReader> is re-exported for type-safe usage
=item add C<expandPaths> prop — forwarded to the default preview C<<Podlite>> renderer for glob-pattern resolution in C<=include file:**/*.podlite>. Type C<ExpandPaths> is re-exported

=head1 0.0.44

=item add C<onSaveAsset> prop — paste/drop image handler. Clipboard paste (PNG/JPEG/GIF/WebP) and drag-drop (same plus SVG) are routed through the callback, which returns a relative path; the editor inserts C<=picture path> at the cursor. No-op when prop is absent
=item fix performance: in full-preview mode skip C<view.dispatch({scrollIntoView:true})> and C<getBoundingClientRect> calls on the hidden CodeMirror view; coalesce preview scroll tracking to one C<getScrollMap> pass per frame via C<requestAnimationFrame>; apply the recorded line in a single dispatch on mode exit
=item fix UX: entering full-preview scrolls the preview to the editor's current top visible line (was always line 1); leaving full-preview places the cursor on the last visible preview line and centers it at ~1/4 from the top of the editor
=item add CSS containment (C<contain: layout paint style>) to C<.line-src> wrappers and C<.podlite-editor-preview> to reduce per-paint cost during scroll
=item add C<content-visibility: auto> + C<contain-intrinsic-size: auto 2em> on C<.line-src> in full-preview mode (gated by C<data-full-preview="true"> attribute) so off-screen blocks skip layout/paint until near viewport

=head1 0.0.43

=item add C<enableFolding> prop — control fold gutter visibility (default C<true>, C<false> for embedded editors)
=item fix embedded editor preview: align first element with editor, reduce list item spacing
=item fix C<WindowWrapper> overflow — add C<max-width: 100%> and restore C<margin: 2rem> on C<.window>
=item fix fold gutter width compensation when folding disabled (C<padding-left: 11px>)

=head1 0.0.42

=item fix performance: eliminate synchronous re-renders on keystroke (text state → ref, deferred onChange via rAF, 300ms debounced preview)
=item fix performance: cache verbatim ranges in fold service (O(N) per call → O(1) via document identity cache)
=item fix search panel closing after Enter on first result — memoize extensions and basicSetup to prevent CodeMirror reconfiguration on re-render
=item add C<enableCopyPng> prop to C<WindowWrapper> — copies content as PNG to clipboard via C<dom-to-image-more>
=item refactor C<WindowWrapper>: remove dead SVG foreignObject screenshot code, add TypeScript types
=item fix fold markers appearing inside verbatim blocks (C<=code>, C<=comment>, C<=data>, C<=input>, C<=output>)
=item fix cursor not visible on file open — add C<autoFocus> + reset C<initialStateApplied> on file change

=head1 0.0.41

=item add list continuation on Enter: auto-insert C<=itemN> with type prefix preserved (C<[ ]>, C<[x]>→C<[ ]>, C<#>)
=item pressing Enter on empty C<=itemN> (or prefix-only) exits the list
=item add Tab/Shift-Tab to increase/decrease C<=item> nesting level (2-space indent per level)
=item add code folding for C<=begin>/C<=end> blocks and C<=head> sections with fold gutter
=item add C<initialEditorState> and C<onEditorStateChange> props for session state persistence (cursor, scroll, folds)

=head1 0.0.40

=item add C<enableHighlighting> prop to toggle code highlighting in preview (podlite/podlite-desktop#42)

=head1 0.0.39

=item enhanced link handling `L<>`
=item fixed a redraw issue when resizing the application window

